John Wick: Chapter 4 /// (also known as John Wick 4 or simply JW4) is an upcoming American neo-noir action thriller film which is serving as the direct sequel to 2019's John Wick: Chapter 3 – Parabellum, as well as the fourth installment in the John Wick film series. Directed by Chad Stahelski, with a script co-written by Shay Hatten and Michael Finch, and based on characters created by Derek Kolstad, it is produced by Stahelski, Basil Iwanyk and Erica Lee. Starring Keanu Reeves returning as the title character, filming took place in Berlin, Paris, Osaka and New York City from June to October 2021. The film is produced by Thunder Road Pictures and 87North Productions and will be distributed by Lionsgate in the United States on March 24, 2023. Originally set for release on May 21, 2021, the film was delayed due to the COVID-19 pandemic and partially due to Reeves' commitments with The Matrix Resurrections.
